		"name": "Document Management API Documentation",
		"description": "# ðŸš€ Get started here\n\nWelcome to the Document Management API, a powerful tool for managing and sharing documents with ease. This API allows users to perform a variety of actions including creating, updating, deleting documents, sharing documents with others, and managing access to documents with fine-grained control.\n\n## ðŸ”– Authentication\n\nBefore using any of the functionalities provided by this API, users must authenticate themselves. This is achieved through the following endpoints:\n\n- `POST /signup`: Allows users to create a new account by providing necessary information such as username, email, and password.\n    \n- `POST /login`: Enables users to authenticate themselves by providing their credentials (username/email and password) and receiving a token in response, which must be included in subsequent requests for authorization.",
